<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Disclaim" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Disclaim,</orth> to disown, to disavow; absol.: <cit><quote>let my --ing from a purposed evil free me so far,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.252" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 252</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>nature --s in thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 59</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>In</emph>).<lb />Transitively: <cit><quote>I have --ed Sir Robert and my land,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.247" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 247</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.490" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 490</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 115</bibl>.
